.TH NTP 1 
.SH NAME
NTP \- Network Time Protocol
.SH "SEE ALSO"
The NTP distribution does not include man pages. To learn more about the NTP 
protocol and this software, please install the 
.B xntp-doc 
package included in you SuSE Linux distribution.
.PP
In 
.I /usr/share/doc/packages/xntp-doc
you will find the complete set of documentation on building and configuring a 
NTP server or client. The documentation is in the form of HTML files suitable 
for browsing and contains links to additional documentation at various web sites.
.PP
Also included: 
.B What about NTP? 
Understanding and using the Network Time Protocol. 
A first try on a non-technical Mini-HOWTO and FAQ on NTP. Edited by Ulrich Windl
and David Dalton.
.PP
Further information on NTP in the Internet can be found in the 
.B NTP web page 
at
.I http://www.eecis.udel.edu/~ntp/
